about.summary: Original idea was presented in the thesis "A statistical analysis tool for agricultural research" to obtain the degree of Master on science, National Engineering University (UNI), Lima-Peru. Some experimental data for the examples come from the CIP and others research. Agricolae offers extensive functionality on experimental design especially for agricultural and plant breeding experiments, which can also be useful for other purposes. It supports planning of lattice, Alpha, Cyclic, Complete Block, Latin Square, Graeco-Latin Squares, augmented block, factorial, split and strip plot designs. There are also various analysis facilities for experimental data, e.g. treatment comparison procedures and several non-parametric tests comparison, biodiversity indexes and consensus cluster.

name: r-agricolae
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3-2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-agricolae
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/agricolae_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/agricolae/agricolae_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ae2205342403ef70fdbc25e78670328eb391a9228c99b097e86c1a4675ad17bd

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-algdesign
    - r-mass
    - r-cluster
    - r-klar
    - r-nlme
    - r-spdep
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-algdesign
    - r-mass
    - r-cluster
    - r-klar
    - r-nlme
    - r-spdep

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('agricolae')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('agricolae')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://tarwi.lamolina.edu.pe/~fmendiburu
  license: GPL
  summary: Original idea was presented in the thesis "A statistical analysis tool for agricultural
    research" to obtain the degree of Master on science, National Engineering University
    (UNI), Lima-Peru. Some experimental data for the examples come from the CIP and
    others research. Agricolae offers extensive functionality on experimental design
    especially for agricultural and plant breeding experiments, which can also be useful
    for other purposes. It supports planning of lattice, Alpha, Cyclic, Complete Block,
    Latin Square, Graeco-Latin Squares, augmented block, factorial, split and strip
    plot designs. There are also various analysis facilities for experimental data,
    e.g. treatment comparison procedures and several non-parametric tests comparison,
    biodiversity indexes and consensus cluster.
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
